#: src/utils.c:45
#, c-format
msgid ""
"Usage: xnec2c [options] [<input-file-name>]\n"
"  -i|--input         <input-file-name>\n"
"  -c|--config        <config-file-path>     - file must exist\n"
"  -C|--new-config    <new-config-file-path> - creates the file when missing\n"
"  -j|--jobs  <number of processors in SMP machine> (-j0 disables forking)\n"
"     --openblas-threads <n>  set OpenBLAS thread count (default: 1)\n"
"     --mkl-threads <n>       set Intel MKL thread count (default: 1)\n"
"     --omp-threads <n>       set OpenMP thread count (default: 1)\n"
"  -b|--batch:        enable batch mode, exit after the frequency loop runs\n"
"  -P|--no-pthreads:  disable pthreads and use the GTK loop for debugging\n"
"  -h|--help:         print usage information and exit\n"
"  -V|--version:      print xnec2c version number and exit\n"
"  -v|--verbose:      increase verbosity, can be specified multiple times\n"
"  -d|--debug:        enable debug output (-dd includes backtraces)\n"
"  -d|--quiet:        suppress debug/verbose output\n"
"\n"
"  --optimize:        Activate the optimizer immediately.\n"
"  --skip-verify:     skip geometry verification checks\n"
"\n"
"The following arguments write to an output file after the frequency loop\n"
"completes.  These are useful to combine with --batch; If you wish to "
"specify\n"
"filenames to write without --batch mode then enable the File->Optimizer\n"
"Settings or the files you specify on the command line will not be written.\n"
"\n"
"  --write-csv             <filename>  - write CSV file of measurements\n"
"  --write-s1p             <filename>  - write S1P file of S-parameters\n"
"  --write-s2p-max-gain    <filename>  - write S2P file, port-2 is max-gain\n"
"  --write-s2p-viewer-gain <filename>  - write S2P file, port-2 is viewer-"
"gain\n"
"  --write-rdpat           <filename>  - write CSV of the radiation pattern\n"
"  --write-currents        <filename>  - write CSV of currents and charges\n"
"  --write-gnuplot-structure <filename> - write gnuplot structure file\n"
"  --write-patch-currents  <filename>  - write CSV of patch surface currents\n"
msgstr ""
"Gebruik: xnec2c [opsies] [<invoerlêernaam>]\n"
"  -i|--input         <invoerlêernaam>\n"
"  -c|--config        <konfigurasielêerpad>     - lêer moet bestaan\n"
"  -C|--new-config    <nuwe-konfigurasielêerpad> - skep die lêer as dit "
"ontbreek\n"
"  -j|--jobs  <aantal verwerkers in SMP-masjien> (-j0 deaktiveer forking)\n"
"     --openblas-threads <n>  stel OpenBLAS-draadtelling (verstek: 1)\n"
"     --mkl-threads <n>       stel Intel MKL-draadtelling (verstek: 1)\n"
"     --omp-threads <n>       stel OpenMP-draadtelling (verstek: 1)\n"
"  -b|--batch:        aktiveer bondelmodus, verlaat nadat die frekwensielus "
"loop\n"
"  -P|--no-pthreads:  deaktiveer pthreads en gebruik die GTK-lus vir "
"ontfouting\n"
"  -h|--help:         druk gebruiksinligting en verlaat\n"
"  -V|--version:      druk xnec2c-weergawenommer en verlaat\n"
"  -v|--verbose:      verhoog breedsprakigheid, kan meervoudig gespesifiseer "
"word\n"
"  -d|--debug:        aktiveer ontfoutingsuitset (-dd sluit terugspore in)\n"
"  -d|--quiet:        onderdruk ontfoutings/breedsprakige uitset\n"
"\n"
"  --optimize:        Aktiveer die optimeerder onmiddellik.\n"
"  --skip-verify:     slaan geometrie-verifikasiekontroles oor\n"
"\n"
"Die volgende argumente skryf na 'n uitsetlêer nadat die frekwensielus "
"voltooi.\n"
"Hierdie is nuttig om met --batch te kombineer; As u lêername wil "
"spesifiseer\n"
"om te skryf sonder --batch-modus, aktiveer dan die Lêer->Optimeerder-\n"
"instellings of die lêers wat u op die opdraglyn spesifiseer sal nie geskryf\n"
"word nie.\n"
"\n"
"  --write-csv             <lêernaam>  - skryf CSV-lêer van metings\n"
"  --write-s1p             <lêernaam>  - skryf S1P-lêer van S-parameters\n"
"  --write-s2p-max-gain    <lêernaam>  - skryf S2P-lêer, poort-2 is maks-"
"aanwins\n"
"  --write-s2p-viewer-gain <lêernaam>  - skryf S2P-lêer, poort-2 is kyker-"
"aanwins\n"
"  --write-rdpat           <lêernaam>  - skryf CSV van die stralingspatroon\n"
"  --write-currents        <lêernaam>  - skryf CSV van strome en ladings\n"
"  --write-gnuplot-structure <lêernaam> - skryf gnuplot struktuurlêer\n"
"  --write-patch-currents  <lêernaam>  - skryf CSV van patch-oppervlakstrome\n"

